A candle 25 cm tall burns at the rate of 5 cm per hour. What percent of the original candle is left after it has burned for 2 hours?
}

\textbf{Answer:} After two hours, the candle will have burned through $2 × 5 \text{cm} = 10$ cm of wax, leaving 15 cm of the candle. This is $\displaystyle \frac{15 \text{cm}}{25 \text{cm}}
= \boxed{60\
}
